# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# distorted.global — Environment configuration
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (which is gitignored) and fill in the
# values. The site runs in graceful "no Shopify" mode if these are
# missing — catalog pages render an empty state, the cart is hidden —
# so you can develop other features before the credentials arrive.
#
# Each NEXT_PUBLIC_-prefixed variable is exposed to the browser.
# Storefront API tokens are designed to be public (read-only product
# data + unauthenticated cart mutations); admin tokens are NOT. Never
# add a Shopify Admin API token to this file.
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Your Shopify store domain. Format: <handle>.myshopify.com
# Found in Shopify admin → Settings → Domains.
# Use the .myshopify.com domain (NOT the custom domain) — the
# Storefront API endpoint is hosted there.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SHOPIFY_STORE_DOMAIN=your-store.myshopify.com

# Storefront API access token.
# To create:
#   Shopify admin → Settings → Apps and sales channels → Develop apps
#   → Create an app → Configure Storefront API integration → enable:
#     unauthenticated_read_product_listings
#     unauthenticated_read_product_inventory
#     unauthenticated_write_checkouts
#     unauthenticated_read_checkouts
#   → Install app → copy the Storefront API access token.
# This token is rate-limited per-IP and read-only; safe to expose.
NEXT_PUBLIC_SHOPIFY_STOREFRONT_ACCESS_TOKEN=your-storefront-token

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Klaviyo (Prompt 8) — Early Access form + back-in-stock notifications
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Three values required. Without them, the API routes
# (/api/klaviyo/subscribe and /api/klaviyo/back-in-stock) return a
# 503 "service unavailable" — forms still render and validate, but
# show the friendly "service temporarily unavailable" copy on submit.
#
# The PRIVATE key is server-only — it's read by /lib/klaviyo/client.ts
# inside our API routes. NEVER prefix it with NEXT_PUBLIC_.
#
# To create:
#   Klaviyo dashboard → Settings → Account → API Keys
#   → Create Private API Key
#   → Scopes: at minimum `Lists: Read/Write`, `Profiles: Read/Write`,
#             `Subscriptions: Read/Write`, `Catalogs: Read/Write`,
#             `Back In Stock: Read/Write`.
KLAVIYO_PRIVATE_KEY=pk_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Public API key — currently unused by server code but reserved for
# future client-side analytics events (Klaviyo's onsite tracker).
# Safe to expose to the browser.
NEXT_PUBLIC_KLAVIYO_PUBLIC_KEY=

# Klaviyo list ID for the Early Access list.
# To find:
#   Klaviyo dashboard → Lists & Segments → click your list
#   → the ID is in the URL (e.g. .../lists/AbC123 → id is "AbC123")
# Owner action item: create a list named "Early Access" before launch.
KLAVIYO_LIST_ID_EARLY_ACCESS=

# Klaviyo welcome email — Klaviyo-side automation, not env config.
# Owner action item: create a flow in Klaviyo that triggers when a
# profile is added to the Early Access list, sending a welcome email.

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Future / not-yet-wired (placeholders for downstream prompts)
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Cloudflare Images (Prompt 10) — lookbook image CDN
# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# When the owner uploads real lookbook photography to Cloudflare
# Images (spec §9), set the delivery URL here:
#
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUDFLARE_IMAGES_DELIVERY_URL=https://imagedelivery.net/<account-hash>
#
# The lookbook config (/config/lookbook.config.ts) currently uses
# picsum.photos placeholders. To migrate, replace each `src` and
# `srcHighRes` with Cloudflare URLs of the form:
#   ${DELIVERY_URL}/<image-id>/public          (in-page ~1400px)
#   ${DELIVERY_URL}/<image-id>/zoom            (lightbox ~2400px)
# where `public` and `zoom` are Cloudflare Image Variants the owner
# defines in Cloudflare dashboard (Image Resizing → Variants).
#
# Next.js Image will run these URLs through Vercel's optimizer for
# additional WebP/AVIF transforms. The next.config.js remotePatterns
# already includes imagedelivery.net.
#
# NEXT_PUBLIC_CLOUDFLARE_IMAGES_DELIVERY_URL=

